.Dd November 27, 2025
.Dt PLAKAR-PKG-ADD 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm plakar-pkg-add
.Nd Install Plakar plugins
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm plakar pkg add Ar plugin ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm plakar pkg add
command adds a local or a remote plugin.
.Pp
If
.Ar plugin
matches an existing local file, it is installed directly.
Otherwise, it is treated as a recipe name and downloaded from the Plakar plugin
server which requires a login via the
.Xr plakar-login 1
command.
.Pp
Installing plugins without logging in is possible via the
.Xr plakar-pkg-build 1
command
.Pq provided you have a working Go toolchain available .
.Pp
To force local resolution use an absolute path, otherwise to
force remote fetching pass an HTTP or HTTPS URL.
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa ~/.cache/plakar/plugins/
Plugin cache directory.
Respects
.Ev XDG_CACHE_HOME
if set.
.It Pa ~/.local/share/plakar/plugins
Plugin directory.
Respects
.Ev XDG_DATA_HOME
if set.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr plakar-login 1 ,
.Xr plakar-pkg-build 1 ,
.Xr plakar-pkg-create 1 ,
.Xr plakar-pkg-rm 1 ,
